main event: Multiple sightings of an unidentified circular flying object in Kenya, Africa in 1950, observed by a civilian couple and a British army captain.
interesting points: The object was described as circular, smooth, and emitting a pearly iridescence, displaying erratic movements and a high-pitched buzz-like sound.
It appeared to move at an incredibly rapid rate, hovering and spinning, and then darting back and forth before taking off at tremendous speed.

The civilian couple initially mistook the object for a flying saucer due to its unusual appearance, while the British army captain observed a metallic silver disc-like object without visible means of propulsion.
The sightings occurred in broad daylight and were witnessed by multiple individuals, adding credibility to the reports.
Despite the detailed observations, there were no photographs included in the document, leaving the sightings unexplained.
